I have an important question for my student and teacher friends, if you have a spare moment.For my capstone CS course, we have been tasked with developing a web-based learning platform of some sort. We are asked to "integrate opportunities offered by emerging technologies with advances in what is known about how people learn." Possible projects might involve intelligent test assessment to allow for adaptive teaching, tools for organizing learning materials, platforms for student participation or discussion, ways to solicit feedback from relevant communities in addition to just the course instructor, educational games, etc. To all you students and teachers out there, any thoughts? I'm looking just as much to identify problems as for potential solutions. What gets in the way of you learning certain things? What might help? (Many thanks to my teammate Christopher, for the post idea)

Join us for our inaugural SBCS Tech Night! We're kicking off our weekly series with a tech talk and workshop on Git, a source control system that allows you to share your code easily with others. It has become a standard way for people to collaborate on code and essentially mandatory knowledge for the best industry and academic software jobs. Our first guest lecturer is a developer at Fog Creek Software in NYC. We will be learning how to create and manage git repositories, and use them with others on a team. Everyone is welcome!

“Things didn’t work out because, well, greater things were in the works. It’s so difficult while we’re blind and hurting and don’t know which way is up. But, if you have faith in anything, have faith in the fact that the universe has a beautiful way of straightening things out far better than we ever could. You may not see it today or tomorrow, but you will look back in a few years and be absolutely perplexed and awed by how every little thing added up and brought you somewhere wonderful– or where you always wanted to be. You will be grateful that things didn’t work out the way you once wanted them to.”

“It is okay to be at a place of struggle. Struggle is just another word for growth. Even the most evolved beings find themselves in a place of struggle now and then. In fact, struggle is a sure sign to them that they are expanding; it is their indication of real and important progress. The only one who doesn’t struggle is the one who doesn’t grow. So if you are struggling right now, see it as a terrific sign — celebrate your struggle.”
